	<h1>About Little Boracay Calatagan, Batangas</h1>

	<p>
		Little Boracay is a popular sandbar destination located in Calatagan, Batangas. 
		Known for its fine white sand and shallow turquoise waters, it offers visitors 
		a coastal experience similar to Boracay Island — but much closer to Metro Manila.
	</p>

	<p>
		The sandbar is accessible by boat from Calatagan’s coastal barangays. 
		Visitors typically arrange boat transfers and floating cottage rentals 
		for day trips, swimming, and group outings.
	</p>

	<h2>What Makes Little Boracay Unique?</h2>

	<p>
		Unlike traditional beach resorts, Little Boracay is a natural sandbar that appears 
		depending on tide conditions. Its shallow waters and wide sand area make it ideal 
		for families, group gatherings, and relaxed beach days.
	</p>

	<ul>
		<li>White sand and crystal-clear shallow waters</li>
		<li>Floating bamboo cottages for day use</li>
		<li>Boat tours from Calatagan town</li>
		<li>Accessible weekend getaway from Manila</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Location and Accessibility</h2>

	<p>
		Little Boracay is situated off the coast of Calatagan in Batangas Province. 
		The travel time from Metro Manila is approximately three to four hours by land, 
		followed by a short boat ride to the sandbar.
	</p>

	<p>
		Because access depends on tide and weather conditions, visitors are encouraged 
		to check local arrangements before planning their trip.
	</p>

	<h2>Our Purpose</h2>

	<p>
		This website provides clear and accurate information about Little Boracay 
		in Calatagan, including travel details, activities, and what visitors can expect. 
		Our goal is to help travelers plan safe and enjoyable coastal experiences 
		in Batangas.
	</p>

